rComments: Dr. Reimer is a wonderful professor, her lectures are interesting and she is very approachable. She is there to help students succeed and is down right a great person. The only down side I found was with grading, sometimes a little difficult to know what the criteria was.
Incredibly approachable, however, she is not very clear or easy when it comes to grading. Overall a fantastic professor who really wants to help students succeed.

Christina is a really enjoyable teacher.  She is very relatable, funny, likeable and approachable.  The only problem is that sometimes she as not as knowledgeable on the subject matter as she should be.

The lectures are the most interesting part; the readings are extremly dense.  she manages to make the lectures interesting with little anecdotes and jokes along the way. Tip: you can buy most of the textbooks from any used bookstore for half the price. But the text books are essential.  the grade is based on 2 (Oct + Apr) test and 2 essays (Dec/Feb
